title: H.S. football: Giancaspro leads Wood-Ridge
text:
H.S. football: Giancaspro leads Wood-Ridge October 25, 2015 Last updated: Sunday, October 25, 2015, 1:21 AM The Record Print 
Sophomore quarterback Michael Giancaspro threw two touchdown passes and ran for a score Saturday to lead the host Wood-Ridge football team to a 28-22 win against Queen of Peace, which kept the Blue Devils mathematically alive in the North 1, Group 1 playoff race. 
Senior running back/linebacker Josh Paez also was instrumental in Wood-Ridge’s NJIC Patriot Division victory. Paez rushed for 148 yards on 25 carries, made eight tackles and returned an interception 35 yards for a touchdown in the third quarter for the Blue Devils (4-3). 
ST. MARY 42, BOGOTA 6 (at Rutherford): Senior tailback Derius Stone rushed for 307 yards and four touchdowns on 19 carries for the Gaels on their way to a NJIC Patriot Division win. 
BIG NORTH 
PASCACK VALLEY 35, PASSAIC VALLEY 6 (at Little Falls): Junior running back Matt Urrea ran for 82 yards and two touchdowns on just three carries for the Indians, ranked No. 5 in The Record Public Top 20. 
Senior quarterback Colin Dedrick also completed 11 of 18 passes for 134 yards and a touchdown for Pascack Valley (6-1). 
DUMONT 35, DWIGHT MORROW 20 (at Englewood): Senior quarterback Sean McCabe gained 75 yards and scored a touchdown on six carries for the Huskies and threw a pair of touchdown passes to junior tight end Daniel Feliciano. Senior Tanner Leuck made nine tackles, defended three passes, forced two fumbles, recovered a fumble and caught a touchdown for Dumont (3-4) as well. 
BISHOP GORMAN 30, DON BOSCO 16 (at Las Vegas): The visiting Ironmen became the first team all season to take a lead on the Gaels, but it wasn’t enough to keep Bishop Gorman from chalking up its 33rd straight win Friday night. 
Bishop Gorman coach Kenny Sanchez called Don Bosco (4-3) the best team the Gaels have faced all season. 
The Ironmen opened a 7-0 lead on a touchdown run by senior tailback Malik Bakker in the first quarter, but the Gaels scored the next 17 points. 
Bishop Gorman (9-0) went ahead, 23-10, with 1:31 remaining in the third quarter, but Don Bosco came back. The Ironmen cut the lead to 23-16 on a three-yard touchdown pass from junior quarterback Tommy DeVito to senior receiver John Bowen with 5:17 to go in the game. 
Bishop Gorman sealed the win with a final 65-yard drive, scoring on a one-yard run by junior Biaggio Walsh with1:30 remaining.
